Architecture review completed successfully for `006D2C`, `006E2`, `006F`, and `006F2` from fixed point `d29f697`. No production code or protected files were changed.

Key findings:

- Legacy appraisals can be marked `verified` without positive audit evidence for both prerequisite assessments.
- Appraisal review checks the permission but does not enforce the source-required Credit Manager role.
- Returned-review reasons are overwritten by later reviews and cannot be recovered from metadata-only audit logs.
- `006D2C` merged without its mandatory PostgreSQL concurrency tests executing; only SQLite skips were recorded.
- Rejected review uses an inverse application/appraisal lock order, creating a potential deadlock.

Corrective work:

- Accepted [ADR-0004](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/docs/adr/ADR-0004-append-only-appraisal-review-decisions.md), shaped by the codebase-design skill to keep immutable review history behind `AppraisalWorkflow`.
- Created [006E3](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/docs/slices/006E3-appraisal-history-and-review-authority-hardening.md) for provenance, Credit-Manager-only authority, and append-only review history.
- Created [006F3](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/docs/slices/006F3-appraisal-lock-order-and-postgresql-concurrency-closure.md) for lock ordering and mandatory zero-skip PostgreSQL concurrency evidence.
- Sharpened `006G` to depend on `006F3`.

Validation passed:

- Django check and migration sync
- 361 backend tests, with two explicit PostgreSQL-only skips
- 95% backend coverage, above the 85% floor
- Frontend lint and typecheck
- 107 frontend tests
- Production build
- Protected-path, artifact-manifest, state, and diff checks

The complete findings and evidence are in [REVIEW_FINDINGS.md](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/docs/working/REVIEW_FINDINGS.md) and the [review packet](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/.ralph/runs/2026-07-10_190455_architecture_review/review-packet.md). Next sequence: `006E3` → `006F3` → `006G`.
